---
title: Cod en Papillote with Brown Butter Caper-Sauce, Dill, and Red Pepper-Potato Hash
description: Cooking “en papillote” is a French technique in which food is cooked inside a parchment (or foil) envelope. The envelope traps all the flavors, resulting in a moist, delicious dish. We’re using this technique to steam delicate cod with garlic and lemon. A buttery caper sauce is the pièce de résistance.
